      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PURO (10) is fresh here off a 100-day break after some good performances at Albany and Pinjarra to end last campaign. She'll carry no weight after the claim of Li and she looks to get her chance on the map. Can resume on a positive note. STAR POWER (3) was very good off a freshen last start at Rockingham, just missing by 0.2L. She's a track and trip winner in the past and she boasts a good record when second-up off a break. Nicely placed and can get the job done. ESQUEL (1) finished off last campaign with a tenth over 1000m at Caulfield Heath on March 4 and has since switched trainers. Goes well when fresh with a win and one minor placings from three starts. One of the primary contenders. CASSENITE (4) proved too strong two runs ago but was not as effective last time out when seventh over 1200m at Pinjarra, beaten 7 lengths. In contention this time. FAMEUX (2) is better than she showed last start and can bounce back.",
